<P>
 Fuller Brush Changes Hands: Fuller Brush Co. is being sold again, this time to 
CPAC Inc., a Leicester, N.Y.-based chemical manufacturer.Fuller Brush, founded 
in 1906 by Coffman Shenk of Gettysburg, Pa., became a household name through 
door-to-door sales of brushes, cleansers and other home necessities by more 
than 12,000 sales representatives. Under the tentative agreement, CPAC will 
acquire all assets and certain liabilities of Fuller Brush, taking a heavy debt 
burden off a group of Kansas-based investors who bought the company from Sara 
Lee Corp. in 1989. The Fuller acquisition will boost CPAC's business by 50%, 
the company said. 
