<P>
 American Telephone + Data Inc.: The company said Friday that it, in 
conjunction with a Portland, Ore., firm, is acquiring SelecTel Corp. of Costa 
Mesa, a company that has been involved in installing telecommunications systems 
on military bases. 
</P>
<P>
 Terms were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 American Telephone in Newport Beach, a holding company specializing in 
telecommunications, is making the acquisition with the Portland consulting firm 
Telephone Management Corp. as a partner. 
</P>
<P>
 SelecTel has about 10 employees. American Telephone Vice President William J. 
Hickey said the personnel and management will all be retained. In addition, "we 
are almost certainly going to be hiring more people," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 American Telephone closed Friday at $2 a share, down 25 cents, in trading on 
the Nasdaq. 
