<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLLYWOOD PARK BOUT CANCELED; BOWE AILING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Riddick Bowe-Larry Donald heavyweight fight at Hollywood Park on July 15 
has been canceled, it was announced Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Hampered recently by back spasms that have left him unable to train, Bowe also 
was forced to cancel a June 11 fight in Las Vegas with Buster Mathis Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 Due to the fight, post time on July 15 had been changed to 12:30 p.m., but 
will now be the usual Friday start at 7 p.m. BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
