<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; DISNEYWORLD INFERNO? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ISABELLE MAELCAMP, Times Brussels Bureau 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The weather is a serious topic of discussion in Belgium because of the big 
temperature difference between Florida and a mostly cold and rainy Europe. 
</P>
<P>
 "Georges Grun and his partners are preparing to live through an inferno on the 
grill of Orlando's Citrus Bowl campus," the French-language daily Le Soir says 
in Brussels. 
</P>
<P>
 In a front-page story, Le Soir explains its surprise at the lack of enthusiasm 
in the World Cup among Americans, saying that ABC will show only 11 of the 52 
World Cup matches. It adds: "Nonetheless, this 1994 World Cup is surely 'on a 
planet scale' the major event of this end of the century." 
</P>
