<P>
 Palo Alto seems ready for its World Cup opener today, featuring Brazil against 
Russia. 
</P>
<P>
 El Camino Real, the main street that runs past Stanford Stadium, where six 
games will be played, has perhaps more soccer banners per square yard than any 
place else in the world. 
</P>
<P>
 About every 50 yards or so, you can see Striker, the logo mascot, making that 
save with his mouth. BILL DWYRE 
