<HEADLINE>
<P>
GONZALEZ PACES O.C. ALL-STARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tony Gonzalez scored 29 points to help a team of Orange County high school 
basketball all-stars rally for a 92-84 victory over the Gold Coast team Sunday 
at Santa Barbara College. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange County outscored Gold Coast, 33-14, in the fourth quarter for the 
victory.Gold Coast, a team of players from the Santa Barbara and Ventura areas, 
dominated the game early and led, 46-36, at the half. 
</P>
<P>
 The lead grew to 62-44 midway in the third quarter, before the Orange County 
all-stars came back with the help of a full-court press and the inside scoring 
of Gonzalez, who is from Huntington Beach High. 
</P>
<P>
 Gil Gonzalez (Orange) and Andy Nieto (Marina) added 11 points each for Orange 
County. Tony Gonzalez had 12 rebounds and Nieto had nine assists. 
</P>
