<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; MUSIC PROGRAM SEEKS ITEMS FOR FUND-RAISER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The parent organization that funds the Pleasant Valley Elementary School 
District's instrumental music program is seeking donations of furniture and 
other items for a garage sale fund-raiser. 
</P>
<P>
 Save Our Kids' Music will hold a garage sale from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. July 1 and 
2 at the Los Primeros Structured School auditorium on Ventura Boulevard in 
Camarillo. 
</P>
<P>
 Under an agreement that Save Our Kids' Music forged with school officials more 
than two years ago, the group reimburses the district for every dollar that it 
spends on the band program. 
</P>
<P>
 The organization is raising money to cover the $7,000 it still owes the 
district for last year, in addition to beginning payments on the estimated 
$52,000 bill for next year. The money primarily covers teachers' salaries. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 200 students in the district are learning to play musical 
instruments through the program. 
</P>
<P>
 Save Our Kids' Music asks the parents of each student who takes music classes 
to contribute $152 per year, but not all parents do. 
</P>
<P>
 People interested in donating items for the garage sale will be able drop them 
off at the Los Primeros auditorium from 6 to 8 p.m. June 25 and 29. 
</P>
<P>
 Save Our Kids' Music will also pick up donated items for no charge. For 
pickup, call Reese Copsey at 484-2415. MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
