<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; LAWS PROPOSED ON ADULT MATERIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Planning Commission tonight will review proposed ordinances that deal with 
adult videos and publications sold in newspaper racks. 
</P>
<P>
 The task before commissioners is deciding what newspaper vending machine 
periodicals are obscene or harmful to minors -- standards the city can use to 
restrict their display on newsstands, Assistant City Atty.Tim Cremin said. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the news rack "blinder" ordinance before the commission, any periodical 
displaying parts of the human anatomy considered obscene would be required to 
cover most of the rack. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposed ordinance includes lengthy definitions of what is considered 
obscene and harmful material, including words, pictures or illustrations 
showing sexual acts. 
</P>
<P>
 The adult video proposal would tighten the city's zoning regulations on where 
and how X-rated videos could be sold and rented. 
</P>
<P>
 After a year of research and public hearings, the City Council recently 
established zoning laws that limit where adult businesses could open in Mission 
Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission will decide whether to recommend the adult video and the 
newspaper rack ordinance to the council, which has the final say on the issue. 
FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
