<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; SWEEPING CONTRACT GOES TO IRVINE FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A one-year street-sweeping contract has been awarded to Irvine-based Sunset 
Property Services, which uses sweepers powered by compressed natural gas. 
</P>
<P>
 The sweepers produce 95% less carbon monoxide and particulate emissions than 
sweepers powered by diesel fuel, company President John Howhannesian said. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's sweepers also use a regenerative air system designed to 
recirculate air inside the vehicle, rather than expel dust and particulates 
into the environment, Howhannesian said. 
</P>
<P>
 The $300,000 contract with the city calls for general sweeping of residential 
and business streets, along with main arterials and city parking lots. 
</P>
<P>
 City Manager Fred Sorsabal said the company was chosen because it has 
demonstrated "a commitment to provide state-of-the-art solutions for cleaning 
the environment, as well as services that are responsive and innovative."ALAN 
EYERLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
