<P>
SEPARATE ACCIDENTS KILL 1, INJURE 1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 84-year-old Huntington Beach motorist was killed and a pedestrian was 
critically injured in two unrelated traffic accidents, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The first accident was about 6 p.m. Saturday on Katella Avenue east of Lewis 
Street when the elderly motorist pulled out of a private driveway and was 
struck by a driver westbound on Katella. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, Harold Gellerman, died at UCI Medical Center in Orange.  
</P>
<P>
 The other accident happened about 9:30 p.m. Saturday when a pedestrian was 
struck by a car as he tried to cross La Palma Avenue near East Street. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, who had yet to be identified by police, suffered head injuries and 
was taken to UCI Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Both accidents are under investigation, police said. 
