<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SOCCER BEATS GOLF IN NATIONAL RATINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The World Cup may turn out to be a television hit in the United States after 
all. 
</P>
<P>
 The U.S.-Switzerland game on Saturday, televised by ABC, beat the third round 
of the U.S. Open, also carried by ABC. The soccer match got an overnight 
national rating of 5.8, the golf a 5.0. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're thrilled with this rating, and pleased we're off to this start," said 
ABC spokesman Mark Mandel. 
</P>
