<HEADLINE>
<P>
SILVA, PIRES WIN VOLLEYBALL TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jackie Silva and Sandra Pires, both of San Clemente, won the women's title at 
the $100,000 Miller Lite Open Pro Beach volleyball tournament Sunday in 
Milwaukee. 
</P>
<P>
 Silva and Pires, originally from Brazil, beat Linda Chisholm and Linda Hanley, 
11-10, 7-6.Both are from Pacific Palisades. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the 46th victory for Silva and the first for Pires who split $5,714. 
</P>
<P>
 Adam Johnson of San Clemente and teammate Randy Stoklos (Pacific Palisades) 
lost in the men's final. They were defeated by Brent Frohoff (Manhattan Beach) 
and Ricci Luyties (San Diego), 15-9. 
</P>
<P>
 The winners split $20,000 and the second-place finishers received $11,400. 
Scott Friederichsen and Leif Hanson, both of Laguna Hills, were third. Fourth 
place went to Troy Tanner and Wes Welch, both of San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Karolyn Kirby and Liz Masakayan, both of San Diego, won the Reebok Hermosa 
Beach women's volleyball open Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Kirby and Masakayan, the top-seeded team, beat Gail Castro of Carlsbad and 
Elaine Roque of Malibu, 15-5, in the title match. 
</P>
